synths.name: TB-303
synths.description: Originally marketed as a bass accompaniment tool, the TB-303 became the cornerstone of acid house music thanks to its resonant, chirpy filter sweeps.

synths.name: Minimoog Model D
synths.description: The definitive monophonic analog synth - prized for its deep basses, soaring leads, and smooth filter. A staple in classic rock, funk, and beyond.

synths.name: Prophet-5
synths.description: The first fully programmable polyphonic analog synth - helped shape the sound of '80s pop and electronic.

synths.name: Juno-106
synths.description: A 6-voice analog poly with signature chorus - favored for pads, brass, and bass in pop and electronic music.
synths.trackExample: “Don't You Forget About Me” - Simple Minds

synths.name: DX7
synths.description: The first commercially successful digital FM synth - famous for its electric pianos and bell tones.

synths.name: Jupiter-8
synths.description: Roland's flagship polyphonic synth - prized for its wide pads, brassy leads, and lush layering.

synths.name: M1
synths.description: A digital workstation famous for the “M1 Piano” and organ - foundational in house and dance music.

synths.name: Odyssey
synths.description: A duophonic analog synth loved for its expressive character - used in funk and fusion.

synths.name: OB-Xa
synths.description: A massive-sounding analog polysynth famous for its brass stabs and huge pads.

synths.name: MS-20
synths.description: A semi-modular mono synth known for its filthy filters and patching capabilities.

synths.name: SH-101
synths.description: A compact mono synth loved for punchy bass and lead sounds - often used live

synths.name: TR-808
synths.description: Not a synth per se, but a programmable analog drum machine whose bass drum became legendary in hip-hop and dance music.

synths.name: D-50
synths.description: Combined samples with synthesis to produce complex, evolving sounds - perfect for '80s ballads.

synths.name: OB-8
synths.description: The final OB-series synth - used by new wave and funk artists for creamy pads and polyphonic leads.
synths.trackExample: “What Have You Done for Me Lately” - Janet Jackson

synths.name: EMS VCS3
synths.description: British modular synth known for sci-fi effects and experimental textures.

synths.name: Voyager
synths.description: Modern analog Moog, with the classic Moog filter and rich sound - used by many electronic artists.

synths.name: PPG Wave
synths.description: A groundbreaking hybrid digital/analog synth featuring wavetable oscillators and analog filters - famous for rich, evolving textures and complex harmonic content.

synths.name: ARP 2600
synths.description: A semi-modular classic used in film scores, early electronic music, and rock - famous for its use in sound design and sci-fi, like R2-D2's voice in Star Wars.

synths.name: Jupiter-4
synths.description: The first Jupiter synth - used for strings, brass, and arpeggios in early synthpop.

synths.name: Blofeld
synths.description: A compact wavetable synth delivering modern textures and evolving pads.
